---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---
<BaseLayout
  title="Ace Combat Online — Multiplayer Guide"
  description="Everything confirmed about Ace Combat Online, the biggest multiplayer mode in Ace Combat 8: Wings of Theve — lobby, avatars, cross-platform play, and Co-Op modes."
>
  <article class="container article">
    <span class="eyebrow">"The franchise's largest online mode" — Bandai Namco</span>
    <h1>Ace Combat Online</h1>

    <p>
      Wings of Theve introduces <strong>Ace Combat Online</strong>, described by producer
      Manabu Shimomoto as the biggest online mode in series history. This is the series'
      first-ever social lobby, and one of the least-covered parts of the game right now —
      which makes it worth bookmarking this page if you're planning to play with friends
      at launch.
    </p>

    <h2>Confirmed so far</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>A persistent <strong>online lobby</strong> set at an air base, where you explore with a customizable avatar before queuing into matches.</li>
      <li><strong>Cross-platform play</strong> between PS5, Xbox Series X|S, and PC.</li>
      <li><strong>Co-Op missions</strong> alongside other multiplayer modes Bandai Namco has said it will detail closer to launch.</li>
      <li>The Ace Pass progression track (free, Premium, and Premium Plus tiers) ties into online play — seasonal rewards include aircraft skins, avatar cosmetics, and upgrade materials.</li>
    </ul>

    <div class="card callout">
      <p class="mono eyebrow" style="margin-bottom:8px;">Still unconfirmed</p>
      <p style="margin:0;">
        Full PvP mode list, matchmaking structure, and cross-play restrictions by platform
        haven't been detailed yet. We're tracking every Bandai Namco dev diary and will keep
        this page current through launch.
      </p>
    </div>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .article {
    padding: 56px 0 80px;
    max-width: 720px;
  }
  .article p, .article li { font-size: 0.98rem; }
  .article ul { padding-left: 20px; }
  .article li { margin-bottom: 8px; }
  .callout { margin: 28px 0; }
</style>
